column686:
2024-05-29 08:32;PMODILAY;[~NLU3] sorry for not clarifying earlier,  the format of data corresponds to process mapping /proc entry, for example:

 
{code:java}
# cat /proc/98346/pmap 
vaddr,size,flags,prot,maxprot,dev,ino,offset,rsv,guardsize,refcnt,mapcnt,path
0x0000000001000000,0x000000000009b000,0x00010071,0x00000005,0x0000000f,0x00000802,0x00000000c0000043,0x0000000000257000,0x0000000000000000,0x0000000000000000,0x000006c0,0x000006be,/proc/boot/libc.so.4
0x000000000109b000,0x0000000000010000,0x080800a2,0x00000000,0x0000000f,0x00000001,0x0000000000000003,0x000000000009b000,0x0000000000000000,0x0000000000000000,0x00000000,0x00000acf,{bss}
...
{code}
So, the second field is the *size* of certain memory mapped to the certain address, which is the first field, the last one - path is actually mapping destination either physical file or memory type - \{heap} in our case, so you can grep the output with "heap";;;

